---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../assets/stylesheets/shapes.css";
import "../styles/global.css";

const pageInfo = {
  title: "Forensic Neuropsychology IMEs - Mind Matters Memphis",
  description:
    "Objective, independent neuropsychological evaluations for worker’s comp, disability, personal injury cases, and more.",
};
---

<Layout page={pageInfo}>
  <div class="bg-dust text-midnight text-xl">
    <div class="bg-sage">
      <div class="headline-top bg-inlet">
        <h1
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl xl:text-6xl 2xl:text-7xl font-accessdisplay font-bold text-dust text-center pt-12 pb-24"
        >
          Forensic Evaluations
        </h1>
      </div>
      <div class="headline-bottom bg-midnight p-4">
        <h1
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl xl:text-6xl 2xl:text-7xl font-accessdisplay font-bold text-sand text-center pt-16 pb-8"
        >
          Objective, Independent Neuropsychological Evaluations
        </h1>
        <div class="grid justify-items-center">
          <div class="text-dust p-4 pb-12 max-w-[624px]">
            <h2 class="font-bold font-accessbold text-2xl pb-2">Offering:</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc grid gap-4">
              <li>
                <p>
                  <a
                    href="#medical-evals"
                    aria-label="Jump to Independent Medical Evaluation section"
                    class="underline">Independent Medical Evaluations</a
                  >
                  {
                    ` (IME) - for workers’ compensation, personal injury cases, and disability`
                  }
                </p>
                <ul class="list-[circle] pl-8 sm:pl-16">
                  <li>Neuropsychological IMEs</li>
                  <li>Psychological-only IMEs</li>
                  <li>Case review and consultation</li>
                  <li>Peer review</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <a
                    href="#testamentary-evals"
                    aria-label="Jump to Testamentary Evaluation section"
                    class="underline pr-1">Testamentary Evaluations</a
                  >- to determine whether a person has the cognitive capacity to
                  create or change their will
                </p>
                <ul class="list-[circle] pl-8 sm:pl-16">
                  <li>
                    This evaluation will assess a person's ability to understand
                    the nature of a will, the extent of their property, who
                    their beneficiaries are, and how they wish to distribute
                    their assets.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <div class="pt-8">
              <p class="italic font-accessitalic">
                <i>
                  For an initial consultation regarding your case, please
                  contact{" "}
                  <a
                    href="tel:+19017667500"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="underline"
                  >
                    901-766-7500
                  </a>{" "}
                  or email{" "}
                  <a
                    href="mailto:info@mindmattersmemphis.com"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    class="underline"
                  >
                    info@mindmattersmemphis.com
                  </a>
                  .
                </i>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid justify-center bg-dust">
        <div
          class="bg-dust p-8 grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-rows-2 max-w-[1000px] gap-8 lg:gap-24 lg:pt-16 lg:pb-0"
        >
          <div id="medical-evals" class="lg:col-span-2">
            <div class="forensic-parallelogram-wrap max-w-[600px]">
              <div
                class="forensic-parallelogram bg-sage flex justify-center items-center w-[100%]"
              >
                <span class="visually-hidden">
                  A decorative parallelogram element, sage green color, framing
                  the header (h2) content.
                </span>
                <div class="drop-shadow-lg h-inherit w-[80%]">
                  <h2
                    class="forensic-parallelogram-lite bg-dust text-midnight font-accessdisplay flex justify-center items-center px-16 text-2xl sm:text-5xl"
                  >
                    <span class="text-center">
                      Independent Medical Evaluations
                    </span>
                  </h2>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-[600px] grid gap-4 pt-8 lg:pt-12">
              <p>
                <span class="font-bold font-accessbold">
                  Neuropsychological Independent Medical Evaluations
                </span>{" "}
                (IMEs) provide an objective assessment of the degree of cognitive
                and emotional decline after an injury or event.
              </p>
              <p>
                Forensic IMEs include a review of the individual’s medical
                history, tests and assessments to evaluate cognitive and
                behavioral function, and a written report to answer a specific
                question posed by the case manager. The results of this IME can
                be used to inform treatment decisions, determine eligibility for
                disability benefits, or provide guidance for legal proceedings.
              </p>
              <!-- <p class="italic font-accessitalic">
                <i>
                  Dr. Gould has experience as a plaintiff's and defense expert
                  witness. Forensic IMEs from Mind Matters Memphis have a rate
                  of $350/hour, and typically require 10-15 hours at a minimum.
                </i>
              </p> -->
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="forensic-chevron rotate-180 hidden bg-sage h-56 lg:block lg:row-start-1 lg:col-start-3 self-center justify-self-center"
          >
            <span class="visually-hidden">
              A decorative chevron (arrow) element, sage green color, pointing
              to the Independent Medical Evaluations text content.
            </span>
          </div>
          <div
            id="testamentary-evals"
            class="lg:col-start-2 lg:col-span-2 lg:justify-self-start"
          >
            <div class="forensic-parallelogram-wrap max-w-[600px]">
              <div
                class="forensic-parallelogram bg-inlet flex justify-center items-center w-[100%]"
              >
                <span class="visually-hidden">
                  A decorative parallelogram element, big sky blue color,
                  framing the header (h2) content.
                </span>
                <div class="drop-shadow-lg h-inherit w-[80%]">
                  <h2
                    class="forensic-parallelogram-lite bg-dust text-midnight font-accessdisplay flex justify-center items-center px-16 text-2xl sm:text-5xl"
                  >
                    <span class="text-center"> Testamentary Evaluations </span>
                  </h2>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-[600px] grid gap-4 pt-8 lg:pt-12">
              <p>
                <span class="font-bold font-accessbold"
                  >Testamentary Evaluations</span
                >{" "}
                are for individuals, families, financial planners, and attorneys
                seeking to protect their wealth or the wealth of their client. These
                cognitive evaluations establish whether an individual has the cognitive
                capacity to create or change a will, which can help safeguard against
                risky decisions or support the soundness of an individual’s decisions.
              </p>
              <p>
                If your client or loved one’s cognition is changing, it may be
                time to have an independent cognitive evaluation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="forensic-chevron hidden bg-inlet h-56 lg:block lg:row-start-2 lg:col-start-1 self-center justify-self-center"
          >
            <span class="visually-hidden">
              A decorative chevron (arrow) element, big sky blue color, pointing
              to the Testamentary Evaluations text content.
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="p-8 pt-0">
      <div class="min-h-40 flex flex-col items-center justify-evenly">
        <p class="max-w-prose md:px-8 sm:pb-4 lg:max-w-fit">
          To learn more about our approach to Cognitive Aging Evaluations, visit
          the Healthy Cognitive Aging page.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/astrosite/cognitive-aging"
          class="bg-dust/80 font-bold font-accessbold sm:text-2xl p-4 px-6 m-4 sm:p-6 sm:px-12 border-2 border-midnight w-fit h-fit justify-self-center rounded-lg transition-all ease-in-out duration-200 relative shadow-md before:absolute before:bottom-[27.5%] before:left-[50%] before:h-[3px] before:w-0 before:origin-center before:rounded-sm before:bg-coral before:transition-all before:duration-300 before:ease-in-out before:content-[''] hover:before:left-[13%] hover:before:w-[74%] sm:hover:before:left-[18%] sm:hover:before:w-[64%] active:left-[1px] active:top-[2px] active:shadow-none"
        >
          Cognitive Aging
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
